article.headline: East Carolina 75, Rice 68
article.story: KATY, Texas (AP) -- Gabe Blair scored 19 points and had 13 rebounds to lead East Carolina to a 75-68 victory over Rice on Wednesday night. East Carolina (11-17, 5-10 Conference USA) used a 15-2 run in the second half to pull away after Rice had taken a 45-44 lead on a layup by Patrick Britton. Cory Farmer and Sam Hinnant each scored 12 for East Carolina. Britton led Rice (3-25, 0-15) with a career-high 40 points. Aleks Perka added 12 for the Owls. Britton scored seven of the Owls' first 10 points and had 21 points by the half. Rice's leading scorer, Rodney Foster, broke his hand in practice Tuesday and is out for the season. The win snapped a 23-game conference road losing streak that dated to 2005.
